WEBVTT

00:01.601 --> 00:02.935
No, seriously,
I think

00:02.936 --> 00:05.037
I've finally figured out
my problem with women.

00:05.038 --> 00:08.741
The capybara is the largest
member of the rodent family.

00:08.742 --> 00:11.177
What does that have to do
with me and women?

00:11.178 --> 00:12.678
Nothing.
It was a desperate attempt

00:12.679 --> 00:15.581
to introduce an alternate topic
of conversation.

00:15.582 --> 00:18.751
My problem is,
I don't project confidence.

00:18.752 --> 00:21.654
So I decided that
the next time I meet a woman

00:21.655 --> 00:23.723
I think is attractive,
rather than holding back

00:23.724 --> 00:25.524
and being cautious,
I'm going to assume

00:25.525 --> 00:27.059
the mantle of self-assurance.

00:27.060 --> 00:28.794
Oh, yeah?
What's that look like?

00:32.399 --> 00:34.633
Hi.

00:34.634 --> 00:37.369
I'm Leonard.

00:37.370 --> 00:39.271
And you are beautiful.

00:39.272 --> 00:42.608
You pop, sparkle
and buzz electric.

00:42.609 --> 00:44.677
I'm going to pick you up
at 8:00,

00:44.678 --> 00:48.781
show you a night
you will never forget.

00:48.782 --> 00:50.616
Where are we going?

00:55.355 --> 00:56.489
Good news.

00:56.490 --> 00:58.324
I made it
onto the team

00:58.325 --> 00:59.525
for the new Defense Department

00:59.526 --> 01:01.277
laser-equipped
surveillance satellite.

01:01.278 --> 01:03.162
Excuse me.

01:03.163 --> 01:05.063
If we're changing topics,
I believe I have first dibs

01:05.065 --> 01:09.135
with capybara, a rodent
the size of a baby hippo.

01:09.136 --> 01:11.454
Congratulations,
Howard.

01:11.455 --> 01:12.705
Thanks.

01:12.706 --> 01:14.907
Listen, I have to get
a security clearance,

01:14.908 --> 01:17.810
so you guys might be
hearing from the FBI.

01:17.811 --> 01:18.878
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

01:18.879 --> 01:20.579
I don't want to speak
to the FBI.

01:20.580 --> 01:21.881
Why not?

01:21.882 --> 01:24.717
I'm brown and I talk funny.

01:24.718 --> 01:27.102
They're just doing
a background check on me.

01:27.103 --> 01:28.487
It doesn't matter;
they'll find a reason

01:28.488 --> 01:30.890
to give me a one-way ticket
back to Gandhi-ville.

01:30.891 --> 01:32.091
By the way,

01:32.092 --> 01:34.126
when I say that,
it's not offensive.

01:34.127 --> 01:36.195
Don't be ridiculous, Raj.

01:36.196 --> 01:37.496
You're here legally.

01:37.497 --> 01:39.131
Nobody cares.
Do you know how long it's been

01:39.132 --> 01:40.466
since I got through
airport security

01:40.467 --> 01:42.668
without being given
a colonoscopy?

01:43.703 --> 01:45.104
You know, I
try very hard

01:45.105 --> 01:47.807
to make our lunch hours
educational and informative,

01:47.808 --> 01:50.643
but your insistence on
talking about your own lives

01:50.644 --> 01:52.478
stymies me at
every turn.

01:52.479 --> 01:55.781
Fine, Sheldon, tell us
about your giant rodents.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.616
1No, you squandered
your time with me,

01:57.617 --> 01:59.468
and the moment
has now passed.

01:59.469 --> 02:01.170
Feast on your disappointment,

02:01.171 --> 02:03.722
much as the capybara
feasts on its own waste.

